'''Bonnievale''' ke toropo nyane wa [[Langeberg Mmusogae]], [[Mmasepala Setereke tša Cape Winelands|Cape Winelands]] go feta [[Kapa Bodikela]], ka moka [[Afrika Borwa]]. 
 
Town 64km south-east of [[Worcester]], in the Breede River Valley. Founded in 1922 and named after the railway siding which had been called Vale since its opening in 1902 and Bonnie Vale in 1917. Municipal status was gained in April 1953.<ref name=dsapn>{{cite web|title=Dictionary of Southern African Place Names (Public Domain)|url=http://archive.org/details/DictionaryOfSouthernAfricanPlaceNames|publisher=Human Science Research Council|page=89}}</ref>

